# “All games” scope

When the user asks to add or wire content into **all games** (including phrases like **“во все игры”**), treat that as a **complete rollout**, not a single screen.

For Unit 9 vocabulary / lexical work, **all games** normally includes, where the content fits:

- **Lexical trainer** — every typed-gap pack listed in the Activity hub (reading, idioms, listening script, sentence completion, prepositional phrases, etc.).
- **Lexical games** — modes that draw from the same pools: Word Bank tick filters, lexical drop, paraphrase pick, express, echo run, paraphrase playback, matching, definition cards, sticky tasks, and any other picker-driven mode in the same hub.
- **Linked flows** — Treasure Hunt, speaking micro / freer lines, and any shared `ensureU9FallPool` / `buildAppLists` consumers when the new content should appear there too.

Do **not** stop after updating one surface unless the user explicitly limits scope. If something is out of scope, say which modes were **not** updated and why.
